descript.abstract: This shapefile was digitized by Fugro Consultants (FCL). An Adobe Illustrator (.ai) file was provided to FCL by the paper's author, Dr. Steven J. Whitmeyer. The .ai file was exported to a high-resolution .bmp and georeferenced. Contacts and boundaries were digitized as lines from the georeferenced image at, or better than a scale of 1:1,000,000. The shapefile lines were then converted to polygon using the ArcGIS software plug-in tool "ET Geowizards" - "build polygons". The polygons were then attributed according to the Precambrian units they represent.
descript.supplinf: Whitmeyer and Karlstrom, "Tectonic model for the Proterozoic growth of North America", Geosphere; August 2007; v.3; no. 4; p. 220-259; doi: 10.1130/GES00055.1;20 figures; 2 animations
